	details = <
		["en"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::en]>
			purpose = <"To organise details of Patient demographics within a standardised record heading as recommended by the UK Academy of Royal Colleges (AoMRC).

Suggested 'subheading' content includes ...

Patient name: The full name of the patient.Also patient preferred name: the name by which a patient wishes to be addressed.
Date of birth: The date of birth of the patient.
Patient sex: Sex at birth. 
Gender: As the patient wishes to portray themselves. 
Ethnicity: The ethnicity of a person as specified by the person.
NHS number: The unique identifier for a patient within the NHS in England and Wales.
Other identifier: Country specific or local identifier, eg, Community Health Index (CHI) in Scotland.
Patient address: Patient usual place of residence. 
Patient telephone: Telephone contact details of the person. To include, eg, mobile, number work and home number if available.
Patient email address: Email address of the patient.
Communication preferences : Preferred contact method, eg, sign language, letter, phone (Also preferred written communication format, eg, large print, braille).
Relevant contacts: Eg next of kin, main informal carer, emergency contact. Name, relationship and contact details.


">
			copyright = <"Â© Clinical Models UK">
			use = <"Current AoMRC guidance does not specify whether 'subheading' content should be computably structured or simply represented by free text.">
		>
	>
